\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} On Windows and macOS the default multiprocessing start method is \PYGZsq{}spawn\PYGZsq{}}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} (or \PYGZsq{}forkserver\PYGZsq{}), which re\PYGZhy{}imports the whole module in every worker.}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} Because the module contains top\PYGZhy{}level executable code, that causes the}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} \PYGZdq{}bootstrapping\PYGZdq{} RuntimeError unless the code is guarded by}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} `if \PYGZus{}\PYGZus{}name\PYGZus{}\PYGZus{} == \PYGZsq{}\PYGZus{}\PYGZus{}main\PYGZus{}\PYGZus{}\PYGZsq{}:`.  The cleanest solution for a self\PYGZhy{}contained}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} script is to keep num\PYGZus{}workers=0 on those platforms (data loading stays}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} in the main process, no subprocesses spawned) and only use workers on}
\PYG{c+c1}{\PYGZsh{} Linux where \PYGZsq{}fork\PYGZsq{} is the default and safe.}
\PYG{n}{\PYGZus{}START\PYGZus{}METHOD} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{multiprocessing}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{get\PYGZus{}start\PYGZus{}method}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{n}{allow\PYGZus{}none}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{k+kc}{True}\PYG{p}{)} \PYG{o+ow}{or} \PYG{l+s+s1}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s+s1}{spawn}\PYG{l+s+s1}{\PYGZsq{}}
\PYG{n}{\PYGZus{}NUM\PYGZus{}WORKERS}  \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb}{min}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{l+m+mi}{4}\PYG{p}{,} \PYG{n}{os}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{cpu\PYGZus{}count}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{p}{)} \PYG{o+ow}{or} \PYG{l+m+mi}{1}\PYG{p}{)} \PYG{k}{if} \PYG{n}{\PYGZus{}START\PYGZus{}METHOD} \PYG{o}{==} \PYG{l+s+s1}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s+s1}{fork}\PYG{l+s+s1}{\PYGZsq{}} \PYG{k}{else} \PYG{l+m+mi}{0}
